headline: Is It Too Late To Consider Johnson Controls International (JCI) After Strong Multi Year Gains?
summary: For investors wondering whether Johnson Controls International is fairly priced or starting to look expensive at its recent levels, this article walks through what the numbers are actually saying about the stock. The share price closed at US$111.29, with returns of 41.2% over 1 year, 73.0% over 3 years and 135.1% over 5 years, even as the stock has seen a 7.1% decline over the last week, a 3.9% decline over the last month and a 9.0% decline year to date.
